%section.tbs-section
  %h1.page-header#alerts Alerts
  %p.lead
    Provide contextual feedback messages for typical user actions
    with the handful of available and flexible alert messages.

  %h2#alerts-examples Examples
  %p
    Wrap any text and an optional dismiss button in
    %code .alert
    and one of the four contextual classes
    (e.g.,
    = succeed ')' do
      %code .alert-success
    for basic alert messages.

  .tbs-example
    .alert.alert-success
      %strong Success!
      You successfully read this important message.
    .alert.alert-info
      %strong Info.
      This alert needs your attention, but it's not super important.
    .alert.alert-warning
      %strong= icon 'exclamation-circle', 'Warning!'
      Better check yourself, you're not looking too good.
    .alert.alert-danger
      %strong= icon 'exclamation-circle', 'Danger!'
      Change a few things up and try submitting again.
